# S17-T2: Realtime server deploy and config
# S17-T2-DeployAndConfig.pd

**Objective:** Set up the realtime server as a runnable artifact: entry point (e.g. server/realtimeServer.ts or a separate package), env (TOTEM_INSTANCES_PATH, PORT, optional REALTIME_WS_URL for client), and how to run it (pnpm run realtime or node dist/realtimeServer.js). Document deploy options (Docker, Railway, Fly, or same host as app) and that it is optional when using Vercel-only.

**Context:**
- Server needs file system access to TOTEM_INSTANCES_PATH; typically same machine or mounted volume. No secrets in repo; env for path and port.
- totem-view client will need the realtime server URL (e.g. ws://localhost:3001 or wss://realtime.example.com) when not using serverless-only mode.

**Gate:** LOCKED

**requires:** [BUILD]

**Steps:**
1. Add realtime server entry (e.g. a new script in package.json "realtime": "ts-node server/realtimeServer.ts" or build and run from server/). Server listens on PORT (default e.g. 3001); reads TOTEM_INSTANCES_PATH from env.
2. Document env vars: TOTEM_INSTANCES_PATH, PORT. Optional: CORS origin for WebSocket if client is on different origin. Document in README or S17 invariants.
3. Document how to run locally (pnpm run realtime alongside pnpm run dev) and how to deploy (e.g. Dockerfile or platform config). State that production can stay Vercel-only and skip this server.
4. Ensure server does not conflict with existing Express server port when both run (e.g. Express 3000, realtime 3001).

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Realtime server can be started via a defined command and env. Deploy and "optional" usage documented.
